---

## Appendix B: Key Reminders

1. **Independence is non-negotiable.** Do not modify any existing editor code. Build everything new.

2. **Preview before production.** Provide a preview link for approval before any integration with live systems.

3. **Context is everything.** The quality of generated pages depends entirely on how well we aggregate and use the Steps 1-7 context.

4. **Frameworks are sacred.** The conversion architecture in each framework is proven. Preserve it while customizing content.

5. **HTML portability is required.** Every page must work perfectly when copied out of the system.

6. **Users own only their pages.** Security isolation must be airtight. Users cannot see, access, or modify anything outside their funnel.

7. **Simplicity wins.** The interface should feel magical, not complicated. Hide complexity, expose capability.

